# Project Scaffold — Cursor Rules
# Last updated: auto-maintained. If your change affects architecture, stack, auth, data,
# routing, env vars, or any public-facing interface → update HANDOFF.md immediately.

## ⚠️ HANDOFF.md is a living document
Whenever you make a change that affects any of the following, you MUST update HANDOFF.md:
- Project structure or file locations
- Auth logic or session handling
- Data shape (users.json, pages.json, prompts.json)
- Environment variables
- API routes (adding, removing, changing method/path)
- Admin UI capabilities
- Page routing conventions
- Deployment or build process
- Any new dependency added to package.json

Do not skip this. HANDOFF.md is the source of truth for any engineer picking this up.

---

## Stack
- Next.js 14, App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS (utility-first, no component libraries)
- Flat JSON files for persistence (/data/*.json)
- JWT in httpOnly cookies for auth
- Anthropic SDK for AI (key in .env.local)

---

## Design System

### Typography
- Font: Inter (Google Fonts), weights 300/400/500
- Default body weight: 300
- Fallback: sans-serif

### Color Tokens (use CSS variables, never hardcode colors)
All colors via hsl(var(--token)) pattern.
Light mode on :root, dark mode on .dark class.

Key tokens: --background, --foreground, --card, --primary, --secondary,
--muted, --accent, --destructive, --border, --input, --ring, --sidebar-*

### Border Radius
- --radius: 0.5rem
- lg: var(--radius), md: calc(var(--radius) - 2px), sm: calc(var(--radius) - 4px)

### Layout Rules
- Max content width: 1080px (max-w-[1080px]) on ALL pages and layouts
- This applies to page content AND navigation/header elements
- Always center constrained content with mx-auto
- Full-bleed backgrounds are fine; only the inner content wrapper is capped

### Aesthetic Rules
- Monochromatic soft grey palette, no strong accent colors
- Subtle shadows only (shadow-sm), never deep/harsh
- Thin borders using --border on all containers and inputs
- Hover: subtle background shift
- Focus: focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring
- Transitions: 0.2s ease-out on interactive elements
- Icons: Lucide React, w-4 h-4 standard, w-3.5 h-3.5 compact
- Spacing: px-4 py-2, gap-2 as base units

---

## File & Folder Conventions
- /app — Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- /app/admin/* — Admin-only routes (middleware-protected)
- /app/(auth)/login — Login page
- /app/test — Demo user-facing page
- /components/ui — Reusable UI primitives
- /components/admin — Admin-specific components
- /data/*.json — Flat file persistence (committed to repo)
- /lib/auth.ts — JWT creation, verification, session helpers
- /lib/data.ts — Read/write helpers for JSON data files
- /lib/prompts.ts — Prompt resolution and variable interpolation

---

## Auth Rules
- Admin: role "admin" in users.json
- Users: role "user", access scoped to allowedPages[] in their record
- JWT stored in httpOnly cookie named "session"
- Middleware at /middleware.ts protects /admin/* and scoped user pages
- JWT_SECRET lives in env only, never in source

---

## Data Rules
- Never hardcode prompts, users, or page configs in source code
- All prompts live in /data/prompts.json, edited only via Admin UI
- All page definitions in /data/pages.json
- All users in /data/users.json
- Writes go through /lib/data.ts — never fs directly in route handlers
- Data files are committed and deployed — they ARE the database

---

## AI / Prompt Rules
- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in .env.local only, never committed
- Prompts fetched at runtime from prompts.json, never hardcoded
- Variables use {{variableName}} syntax
- Interpolation happens server-side in /lib/prompts.ts
- Users never see raw prompt text

---

## API Route Conventions
- All routes under /app/api/
- Auth: /api/auth/login, /api/auth/logout
- Admin: /api/admin/* (middleware-protected)
- AI execution: /api/run-prompt
- Response shape: { success: boolean, data?, error? }

---

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode, no any types
- Functional components only
- Server Components by default; "use client" only when needed
- Named exports for components, default exports for pages
- Keep route handlers thin — logic in /lib
